column14: Section-by-section measurement (SP w/ARC boat #128) from BOC. No apparent angles observed and none entered. Panel location by second tech and rangefinder. Panels: 20. Max. (q/Q): 15.7%. Uncertainty: 3.2%. QA/QC concerns: M1: Water at transect not suitable for compass calibration (too turbulent). CC conducted at parking lot by lazy susan (& attached wooden platform). Magnetic declination obtained by CrowdMag app on-site. No magnetic anomaly detected by app. Large standing waves in vicinity of BOC (15-17m). Shortening and lengthening tether did little to alleviate. MBT loop failed (too much missing data). Loop discarded. Obtained 5 minute stationary mid-channel. Significant missing data in standing waves. Large directional bias (theorized to be due to lazy susan attached to wooden platform). Transects 000 & 001 discarded. M1 measurement discarded. M2: CC conducted at transect with carbon bearing lazy susan & wooden platform. Pass. Same issues with transects: large directional bias large amount of missing data and discharge way too low. Proceeded to section by section. Large standing waves still caused issues (drastic drop in velocities where ARC boat was riding high and nose pulled up). The addition of four ARC batteries in the compartment allowed the boat to sit lower and alleviated the issue in some of the locations. But between 14-17m the boat would not sit low and acquired velocities were obviously too low compared to panels on either side (also large directional SDs). See 10AA005_20220614_M3_BAD_VELOCITIES. This was confirmed visually as well as reviewing past measurement velocity profiles. The only option was to discard the panels between 15 & 17 and extrapolate. This causes a >10 panel at panel 14 & 18 (15.7 & 12.5%). Would high speed boat be better? Woud different tethering to ARC improve it's angle in the water? EXTRAP NOT CONDUCTED. SWIM MEETING GUIDANCE AND ‘HOW TO’ DOCUMENT STATE NOT MANDATORY. Low confidence measurement.  Large surge observed over sensor (paint).  DWL at path from shelter w/stilling bucket.  HWM (debris line - medium confidence): 4.695m.  Depth of sensor at 17:30: DWL(4.409) - Offset(3.107) = 1.302m.  Mid-section
